UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 273/GA
1 AN ACT relating to barbering.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 Section 1. KRS 317.410 is amended to read as follows:
4 As used in this chapter, unless the context requires otherwise:
5 (1) "Barber" means any person who engages in the practice of barbering for the public
6 generally or for consideration;
7 (2) "Barbering" means the practice upon the human neck, face, and head, principally of
8 shaving or trimming the beard or cutting the hair, but includes also:
9 (a) Giving facial and scalp massage or treatments with oils, creams, lotions, or
10 other preparations, either by hand or any contrivance;
11 (b) [Singeing, ]Shampooing, pressing, arranging, dressing, styling, or dyeing the
12 hair or applying hair tonics; and
13 (c) Applying to the neck or head[ cosmetics,] lotions, powders, oils, clays, or
14 other preparations;
15 (3) "Barber pole" means a cylinder or pole with alternating stripes of any combination,
16 including but not limited to red and white, or red, white, and blue, which run
17 diagonally along the length of the pole;
18 (4) "Barber school" or "school of barbering" means an operation, place, or
19 establishment in or through which persons are trained or taught the practice of
20 barbering;
21 (5) "Barber shop" means any establishment in which the practice of barbering is
22 conducted for the general public or for consideration and includes a mobile barber
23 shop;
24 (6) "Board" means the Kentucky Board of Barbering;
25 (7) "Endorsement" means the process of granting a license under this chapter to an
26 applicant licensed in another state;
27 (8) "Independent contract owner" means any barber or apprentice barber licensed under
Page 1 of 12
HB027310.100 - 1436 - XXXX 3/16/2026 5:02 PM GA

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 273/GA
1 this chapter who leases or rents space in a barber shop;
2 (9) "Lapse fees" means the annual renewal license fee which would have been paid for
3 the period during which a license has lapsed; and
4 (10) "Mobile barber shop" means a self-contained unit in which the practice of barbering
5 is conducted and which may be moved, towed, or transported from one (1) location
6 to another.
7 Section 2. KRS 317.420 is amended to read as follows:
8 (1) A[No] person shall not engage in the practice of "barbering" for other than cosmetic
9 purposes nor shall any person engage in barbering for the treatment of physical or
10 mental ailments, except that[ the provisions of] this chapter shall not apply to:
11 (a) Persons authorized by the law of this state to practice medicine, chiropody,
12 optometry, dentistry, chiropractic, nursing, or embalming when incidental
13 practices of barbering are performed by them in the normal course of the
14 practice of their profession;
15 (b) Commissioned medical or surgical personnel of the United States Armed
16 Forces performing incidental practices of barbering in the course of their
17 duties; or
18 (c) Barbering services performed at an institution operated by or under contract to
19 the Department of Corrections or the Department of Juvenile Justice.
20 (2) Except as provided in subsection (1) of this section, a[no] person shall not engage
21 in the practice of barbering for the public generally or for consideration without the
22 appropriate license required by this chapter.
23 (3) A[No] person, unless duly and properly licensed pursuant to this chapter, shall not:
24 (a) Teach barbering;
25 (b) Operate a barber shop or mobile barber shop;
26 (c) Conduct or operate a school for barbers;
27 (d) Lease or rent booth space as an independent contract owner; or
Page 2 of 12
HB027310.100 - 1436 - XXXX 3/16/2026 5:02 PM GA

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 273/GA
1 (e) Operate a mobile barber shop without first notifying the board of its location
2 or change in its location.
3 (4) A[No] person shall not aid or abet any person in violating[ the provisions of] this
4 section, nor shall any person engage or employ for consideration any person for the
5 performance of any practice licensed by this chapter unless the person to perform
6 such practice holds and displays the current appropriate license therefor.
7 (5) Except as provided in this chapter, a[no] person or business shall not:
8 (a) Advertise barbering services, unless the person or business and the personnel
9 it employs are licensed under this chapter;
10 (b) Advertise as a barber shop or mobile barber shop, unless all persons in the
11 shop practicing barbering services are licensed under this chapter. Any barber
12 practicing in a shop licensed as both a barber shop and a salon licensed under
13 KRS Chapter 317A may display an image, that is at least four (4) inches high,
14 of a barber pole at his or her station; or
15 (c) Use or display a barber pole for the purpose of advertising barbering services
16 to the public unless it:
17 1. Has a barber shop license; and
18 2. Employs a barber licensed under this chapter.
19 (6) A person holding an active barber license from the board and who practices in a
20 shop licensed by the board may render services for pay or otherwise to:
21 (a) A person suffering from a terminal illness who is receiving the services of a
22 hospice program either at home or at a hospice inpatient unit; or
23 (b) A person who is deceased and in the care of a funeral establishment.
24 Section 3. KRS 317.430 is amended to read as follows:
25 (1) There is hereby created an independent agency of the state government to be known
26 as the Kentucky Board of Barbering, which shall have complete supervision over
27 the administration of[ the provisions of] this chapter relating to barbers, barbering,
Page 3 of 12
HB027310.100 - 1436 - XXXX 3/16/2026 5:02 PM GA

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 273/GA
1 barber shops, mobile barber shops, independent contract owners, barber schools,
2 and the teaching of barbering.
3 (2) (a) The board shall be composed of five (5) voting members appointed by the
4 Governor. Four (4) of these members shall be barbers holding a valid license
5 and practicing in Kentucky. One (1) of these members[member] shall be a
6 citizen at large who is not associated with or financially interested in
7 barbering. At all times in the filling of vacancies of voting membership on the
8 barber board, this balance of representation shall be maintained.
9 (b) The executive director employed under Section 7 of this Act shall be a
10 nonvoting member of the board. He or she may be counted in determining a
11 quorum, but shall not vote on matters before the board.
12 (3) [The two (2) members appointed to fill the terms beginning on February 1, 2008,
13 shall serve until February 1, 2011, and the three (3) members appointed to fill the
14 terms beginning on February 1, 2007, shall serve until February 1, 2010. ]All
15 [subsequent ]appointments shall be for a term of three (3) years, with terms ending
16 on February 1.
17 (4) The Governor shall not remove any voting member of the board except for cause.
18 (5) The board shall elect from its voting members one (1) to serve as chair[chairman],
19 one (1) to serve as vice chair[chairman], and one (1)[a third] to serve as secretary.
20 (6) Three (3) members shall constitute a quorum for the transaction of business.
21 (7) In addition to the other qualifications specified in this section, voting barber
22 members of the board shall be at least twenty-three (23) years of age, citizens of the
23 United States, residents of Kentucky, and shall[must] have engaged in the practice
24 of barbering in this state for a period of at least five (5) years.
25 (8) A[No] member of the board shall not be financially interested in, or have any
26 financial connection with, any barber or cosmetology school, wholesale cosmetic or
27 barber supply or equipment business, and[nor] shall not[any member of the barber
