1 board] teach barbering, cosmetology, or manicuring for monetary considerations.
2 (9) [Each member of the board shall receive a compensation of one hundred dollars
3 ($100) per day for each day of attendance at a meeting of the board, and shall be
4 reimbursed for necessary traveling expenses.
5 (10) ]The board shall hold its meetings within the state and when deemed necessary by
6 the board to discharge its duties.
7 Section 4. KRS 317.440 is amended to read as follows:
8 (1) To protect the health and safety of the public and to protect the public against
9 misrepresentation, deceit, or fraud in the practice or teaching of barbering, the
10 board shall promulgate administrative regulations governing the:
11 (a) Location and housing of barber shops, mobile barber shops, or schools;
12 (b) Quantity and quality of equipment, supplies, materials, records, and
13 furnishings required in barber shops, mobile barber shops, or schools;
14 (c) Qualifications of teachers of barbering;
15 (d) Qualifications of applicants to or enrollees in barber schools;
16 (e) Hours and courses of instruction at barber schools;
17 (f) Examinations of applicants for barber or teacher of barbering;
18 (g) Qualifications of independent contract owners;[ and]
19 (h) Inspection criteria for mobile barber shops; and
20 (i) Compensation and expense schedule for board members.
21 (2) The board shall establish:
22 (a) Fees by administrative regulation; and
23 (b) On its website a system for a licensed mobile barber shop to:
24 1. Submit to the board a weekly itinerary detailing the locations at which it
25 will offer barbering services; and
26 2. Notify the board of any changes in its location or itinerary[.
27 (3) Administrative regulations pertaining to health and sanitation shall be approved by
