1 13A; and
2 2. Complied with all other requirements of this subsection.
3 (e) The board may issue a barber license by endorsement to a resident of another
4 state, district, or territory within the United States of America upon payment
5 of a fee as established in administrative regulations promulgated by the board
6 in accordance with KRS Chapter 13A, and upon submission of satisfactory
7 evidence that the requirements for licensure in the other state are substantially
8 equivalent to the requirements of this state at the time of application. In the
9 absence of the required equivalency, an applicant from another state, district,
10 or territory within the United States of America, shall show proof of one (1)
11 year[three (3) years] or more experience immediately before making
12 application and be currently licensed and in good standing with the state,
13 district, or territory in which he or she is licensed. The board may also require
14 an applicant under this paragraph[section] to pass a written and practical
15 examination to establish equivalency.
16 (2) The board shall:
17 (a) Issue a license to operate a barber shop or mobile barber shop to any barber
18 licensed under[ the provisions of] this chapter upon application and payment
19 of a fee as established in administrative regulations promulgated by the board
20 in accordance with KRS Chapter 13A;
21 (b) Refuse to issue the license upon a failure of the licensed barber to comply
22 with[ the provisions of] this chapter or the administrative regulations
23 promulgated by the board;
24 (c) Allow the licensed owner of a barber shop or mobile barber shop, which is
25 licensed under this chapter, to rent or lease space in his or her barber shop to
26 an independent contract owner; and
27 (d) Allow an unlicensed owner of a barber shop to rent or lease space in his or her
