11 Section 6. KRS 317.460 is amended to read as follows:
12 (1) The board shall hold hearings upon the request of any person directly affected by
13 the board's decision to refuse a license,[;] deny or revoke a license,[;] or suspend or
14 place a licensee on probation. Hearings shall be conducted in accordance with KRS
15 Chapter 13B.
16 (2) For the purpose of enforcing[ the provisions of] this chapter, officers, agents, and
17 inspectors of the board may enter upon premises of all facilities issued a permit or
18 license by the board, at all reasonable times and during periods when those
19 premises are otherwise open to the public, and make inspections to determine
20 compliance with this chapter and the administrative regulations promulgated by the
21 board, require identification, and inspect books, papers, or records pertaining to
22 licensed activity, a copy of which may be obtained by the board officer, agent, or
23 inspector.
24 (3) Final orders of the board as a result of any hearing may be appealed to the Franklin
25 Circuit Court in accordance with KRS Chapter 13B.
