14 Section 8. KRS 317.540 is amended to read as follows:
15 A[No] license shall not be renewed or issued by the board to any barber school[,] unless
16 the school provides:
17 (1) The name of the proposed school;
18 (2) A statement that the proposed school is authorized to operate educational programs
19 beyond secondary education;
20 (3) As a prerequisite of graduation, a prescribed course of instruction of not less than
21 one thousand two hundred (1,200)[fifteen hundred (1,500)] hours shall be given
22 within a reasonable period with not more than ten (10)[eight (8)] hours nor less than
23 four (4) hours of instruction a day, exclusive of Sundays;
24 (4) Courses of instruction in histology of the hair, skin, muscles, and nerves of the face
25 and neck; elementary chemistry with emphasis on sterilization and antiseptics;
26 disease of the skin, hair, and glands; massaging and manipulating of the muscles of
27 the upper body; cutting, shaving, arranging, dressing, coloring, bleaching, and
