7 Section 9. KRS 317.570 is amended to read as follows:
8 (1) Except as authorized by subsection (4) of this section, no examination or part of any
9 examination required by this chapter shall be given unless two (2) or more members
10 of the board are present to supervise the examination.
11 (2) Examinations given by the board shall cover all phases of the applicant's
12 qualifications for licensure,[the license applied for] including knowledge of this
13 chapter, the skill and technique of the applicant, as well as scientific and other
14 knowledge required by the board to obtain licensure.
15 (3) Examinations shall be given at regularly prescribed intervals.
16 (4) Examinations shall be given at the principal office of the board, except that
17 examinations may be given at a Department of Corrections facility that operates a
18 licensed barber school. Examinations shall be supervised by two (2) or more
19 members of the board, or board staff designated for that purpose, who shall be
20 present at the site of the examination.
